description: Naming conventions for markdown files for when making new markdown files
alwaysApply: false
---
Use `kebab-case.md`

docs/
├── training-recipe.md          # kebab-case
├── architecture-overview.md    # kebab-case
└── design-patterns.md          # kebab-case


**Exception**: For root-level project or package documentation, always use `README.md` in all capital letters (not kebab-case).

Examples:
docs/
├── training-recipe.md          # kebab-case
├── architecture-overview.md    # kebab-case
├── design-patterns.md          # kebab-case
└── README.md                   # exception: all caps

